---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Intelligence | Levenhall" description="Levenhall Intelligence is a real-time defense and geopolitical operating picture — 119 RSS feeds, satellite and conflict data, live media, on-device ML, and a proprietary Country Instability Index, fused into one WebGL global defense map.">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="intel-hero">
        <div class="hero-bg"></div>
        <div class="hero-grid-overlay"></div>
        <div class="hero-scanlines"></div>

        <!-- HUD corner brackets -->
        <span class="hud-bracket hud-tl"></span>
        <span class="hud-bracket hud-tr"></span>
        <span class="hud-bracket hud-bl"></span>
        <span class="hud-bracket hud-br"></span>

        <div class="hero-inner">
            <div class="intel-badge">A Levenhall Product</div>
            <p class="intel-eyebrow">Levenhall</p>
            <h1 class="intel-wordmark">INTELLIGENCE</h1>
            <p class="intel-sub">Real-Time Defense &amp; Geopolitical Operating Picture</p>
            <div class="hero-rule"></div>
            <p class="hero-description">A unified operating picture for allied defense advisory, security analysis, and strategic decision-making. 119 RSS feeds, satellite data, conflict databases, economic indicators, and live media &mdash; fused through on-device machine learning, a proprietary Country Instability Index, and a multi-layered WebGL global defense map.</p>
            <div class="hero-cta">
                <a href="https://intel.levenhall.com" class="btn btn-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Intelligence</a>
                <a href="#modules" class="btn btn-outline-white">See the Modules</a>
            </div>
            <p class="hero-live">Live at <span class="hero-live-url">intel.levenhall.com</span></p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── AT A GLANCE (LIGHT) ── -->
    <section class="section glance-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="glance-grid reveal">
                <div class="glance-card">
                    <span class="glance-value">119</span>
                    <span class="glance-label">RSS Intelligence Feeds</span>
                </div>
                <div class="glance-card">
                    <span class="glance-value">34</span>
                    <span class="glance-label">Global Map Layers</span>
                </div>
                <div class="glance-card">
                    <span class="glance-value">27</span>
                    <span class="glance-label">Dashboard Panels</span>
                </div>
                <div class="glance-card">
                    <span class="glance-value">31</span>
                    <span class="glance-label">Tier-1 Countries</span>
                </div>
                <div class="glance-card">
                    <span class="glance-value">4</span>
                    <span class="glance-label">ONNX Models On-Device</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THE OPERATING PICTURE (LIGHT) ── -->
    <section class="section picture-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="picture-grid reveal">
                <div class="picture-text">
                    <span class="section-label">The Operating Picture</span>
                    <h2>One Screen. Every Signal. No Data Leaves the Browser.</h2>
                    <div class="gold-rule"></div>
                    <p>Levenhall Intelligence fuses signals from across the analyst's information stack &mdash; armed conflict events, civil unrest, military movements, economic indicators, cyber threats, climate anomalies, live media &mdash; into a single, real-time operating picture.</p>
                    <p>Heavy ML inference runs entirely client-side. Four ONNX models &mdash; embeddings, sentiment, summarization, and named-entity recognition &mdash; execute in a Web Worker, in the analyst's own browser, without round-tripping sensitive context to a server.</p>
                    <p>The result is a defense-grade dashboard that loads anywhere there is a browser, scales with the analyst rather than the back end, and demonstrates Levenhall's analytical capabilities in production.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="picture-visual">
                    <div class="picture-card">
                        <span class="picture-card-label">Built For</span>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Allied defense advisory teams</li>
                            <li>Security analysts &amp; G2 staff</li>
                            <li>Federal program offices</li>
                            <li>Strategic decision-makers in regulated sectors</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── SIX MODULES (DARK) ── -->
    <section class="section modules-section" id="modules">
        <div class="modules-bg"></div>
        <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
            <div class="section-header reveal">
                <span class="dark-label">Intelligence Modules</span>
                <h2>Six Layers of Analysis on One Data Spine</h2>
                <p>Each module is a self-contained analytical engine. Signals flow between them through an internal routing layer the platform refers to as BRIDGER &mdash; the signal bridge that links Intelligence to the wider Levenhall product stack.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="modules-grid">
                <div class="module-card module-card-wide reveal">
                    <div class="module-head">
                        <span class="module-num">01</span>
                        <span class="module-tag">Composite Score</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Country Instability Index (CII)</h3>
                    <p>A proprietary 0&ndash;100 composite tracking instability across 31 Tier-1 countries &mdash; the nations most relevant to allied defense posture.</p>
                    <div class="formula-box">
                        <span class="formula-label">Blended Score</span>
                        <code>(Baseline Risk &times; 0.4) + (Event Score &times; 0.6)
+ Hotspot Boost + News Urgency Boost
+ Focal Point Boost + Displacement Boost + Climate Stress</code>
                    </div>
                    <div class="event-mix">
                        <span class="event-mix-label">Event Score Mix</span>
                        <div class="event-mix-bars">
                            <div class="event-mix-row"><span class="emr-name">Conflict</span><div class="emr-bar"><div class="emr-fill" style="width: 30%;"></div></div><span class="emr-pct">30%</span></div>
                            <div class="event-mix-row"><span class="emr-name">Unrest</span><div class="emr-bar"><div class="emr-fill" style="width: 25%;"></div></div><span class="emr-pct">25%</span></div>
                            <div class="event-mix-row"><span class="emr-name">Information</span><div class="emr-bar"><div class="emr-fill" style="width: 25%;"></div></div><span class="emr-pct">25%</span></div>
                            <div class="event-mix-row"><span class="emr-name">Security</span><div class="emr-bar"><div class="emr-fill" style="width: 20%;"></div></div><span class="emr-pct">20%</span></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="module-foot">Modifiers include UCDP conflict floors (active wars score &ge;70), displacement thresholds (&ge;1M displaced adds +8), and per-country event multipliers (0.3&times;&ndash;3.0&times;). Output tiers: <strong>Low &middot; Normal &middot; Elevated &middot; High &middot; Critical</strong>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card reveal">
                    <div class="module-head">
                        <span class="module-num">02</span>
                        <span class="module-tag">Convergence</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Geo-Convergence Detection</h3>
                    <p>Divides the globe into 1-degree grid cells and monitors for multi-source signal convergence within a 24-hour rolling window.</p>
                    <p>When conflict events, protest reports, military movements, and news signals cluster in the same cell, the system flags potential emerging hotspots <em>before</em> they hit mainstream reporting.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card reveal">
                    <div class="module-head">
                        <span class="module-num">03</span>
                        <span class="module-tag">Strategic Risk</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Strategic Risk Composite</h3>
                    <p>One strategic-risk score per region, blending three orthogonal inputs:</p>
                    <ul class="module-list">
                        <li>Geo-convergence signal &mdash; <strong>30%</strong></li>
                        <li>Country Instability Index &mdash; <strong>50%</strong></li>
                        <li>Infrastructure cascade risk &mdash; <strong>20%</strong></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card reveal">
                    <div class="module-head">
                        <span class="module-num">04</span>
                        <span class="module-tag">Signal Bus</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Signal Aggregation &amp; BRIDGER Bridge</h3>
                    <p>A unified signal stream that ingests CII, conflict, unrest, economic, cyber, military, and climate channels.</p>
                    <p>The BRIDGER bridge then routes prioritized signals across modules &mdash; and onward into the broader Levenhall platform stack.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card module-card-wide reveal">
                    <div class="module-head">
                        <span class="module-num">05</span>
                        <span class="module-tag">On-Device ML</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Browser-Side Inference Pipeline</h3>
                    <p>Four ONNX models run entirely in-browser with no server dependency. Semantic clustering uses a 0.75 cosine similarity threshold across batches of 20 texts, inside a 200 MB memory budget. All inference runs in a Web Worker so the UI stays responsive.</p>
                    <div class="ml-table">
                        <div class="ml-row ml-head">
                            <span>Model</span>
                            <span>Purpose</span>
                            <span>Size</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-row">
                            <span class="ml-name">all-MiniLM-L6-v2</span>
                            <span>Semantic embeddings for event clustering</span>
                            <span class="ml-size">23 MB</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-row">
                            <span class="ml-name">DistilBERT SST-2</span>
                            <span>Sentiment classification</span>
                            <span class="ml-size">65 MB</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-row">
                            <span class="ml-name">FLAN-T5 Base</span>
                            <span>Abstractive summarization</span>
                            <span class="ml-size">250 MB</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-row">
                            <span class="ml-name">BERT-base-NER</span>
                            <span>Named entity recognition (people, orgs, locations)</span>
                            <span class="ml-size">65 MB</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="module-card reveal">
                    <div class="module-head">
                        <span class="module-num">06</span>
                        <span class="module-tag">Cascade</span>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Infrastructure Cascade Analysis</h3>
                    <p>Models interdependencies between critical infrastructure systems &mdash; undersea cables, power grids, pipelines, data centers &mdash; to predict how a disruption in one system propagates across others.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── GLOBAL DEFENSE MAP (LIGHT) ── -->
    <section class="section map-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header reveal">
                <span class="section-label">Global Defense Map</span>
                <h2>34 Intelligence Layers on One WebGL Globe</h2>
                <p>The centerpiece of the platform. DeckGL 9.2 + MapLibre GL, defense-HUD aesthetic, gold corner brackets, scan-line overlay, vignette, glass-blur control panels. Eleven layers default-on; the rest toggle from a single panel.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="map-layers reveal">
                <div class="map-group">
                    <h4>Default On <span class="map-group-count">11</span></h4>
                    <div class="map-chips">
                        <span class="map-chip">Conflicts</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Military Bases</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Military Assets</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Sanctions</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Hotspots</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Nuclear Facilities</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Waterways</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Infrastructure Outages</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Natural Disasters</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Economic Indicators</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Weather</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="map-group">
                    <h4>Toggle On <span class="map-group-count">23</span></h4>
                    <div class="map-chips map-chips-muted">
                        <span class="map-chip">Undersea Cables</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Pipelines</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">AIS Maritime Tracking</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Nuclear Irradiators</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Cyber Threats</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Data Centers</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Protests</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Military Flights</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Spaceports</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Critical Minerals</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Satellite Fires</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Displacement Camps</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Climate Anomalies</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Startup Hubs</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Cloud Regions</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Accelerators</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Tech HQs</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Tech Events</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Stock Exchanges</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Financial Centers</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Central Banks</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Commodity Hubs</span>
                        <span class="map-chip">Gulf Investments</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── 27 PANELS (CREAM) ── -->
    <section class="section panels-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header reveal">
                <span class="section-label">Intelligence Panels</span>
                <h2>27 Specialized Modules in the Dashboard</h2>
                <p>Each panel is a self-contained intelligence module. Together they form the analyst's working surface, organized by mission area.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="panels-grid reveal">
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">Strategic</span>
                    <ul><li>Strategic Posture</li><li>Strategic Risk</li><li>CII</li><li>Cascade Analysis</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">Conflict &amp; Security</span>
                    <ul><li>UCDP Events</li><li>Displacement</li><li>Climate Anomaly</li><li>Population Exposure</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">News &amp; Analysis</span>
                    <ul><li>Live News</li><li>News</li><li>GDELT Intel</li><li>Insights</li><li>Monitor</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">Defense &amp; Procurement</span>
                    <ul><li>GeoHubs (defense / intel)</li><li>Investments</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">Markets &amp; Economy</span>
                    <ul><li>Market</li><li>Economic</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">Technology</span>
                    <ul><li>Tech Events</li><li>Tech Hubs</li><li>Tech Readiness</li><li>Regulation</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">Live Media</span>
                    <ul><li>Live Webcams</li><li>Jerusalem · Tehran · Mecca</li><li>NYC · Taipei · Kyiv</li><li>Moscow · Seoul · Beijing</li></ul>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <span class="panel-cat">System</span>
                    <ul><li>Status</li><li>Service Status</li><li>Runtime Config</li><li>Satellite Fires</li></ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── DATA SOURCES (DARK) ── -->
    <section class="section sources-section">
        <div class="sources-bg"></div>
        <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
            <div class="section-header reveal">
                <span class="dark-label">Data Sources</span>
                <h2>119 RSS Feeds &middot; 12 Categories &middot; 8 External APIs</h2>
                <p>Every source is rated against a four-tier credibility system. State-affiliated and known-bias outlets carry explicit propaganda-risk labels.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="sources-grid reveal">
                <div class="source-table">
                    <div class="source-row source-head">
                        <span>Category</span>
                        <span>Feeds</span>
                        <span>Representative Sources</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Defense</span><span class="src-count">10</span><span>Defense One, Breaking Defense, Janes, Military Times</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Think Tanks</span><span class="src-count">18</span><span>CSIS, RAND, Brookings, Carnegie, Chatham House</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Indo-Pacific</span><span class="src-count">9</span><span>ASPI, Lowy Institute, regional security feeds</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Alliances</span><span class="src-count">7</span><span>NATO, AUKUS-related, allied defense ministries</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Procurement</span><span class="src-count">7</span><span>FedBizOpps, SAM.gov, defense acquisition</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Government</span><span class="src-count">6</span><span>White House, State Dept, Pentagon, UK MOD</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Cybersecurity</span><span class="src-count">6</span><span>Krebs, CISA, CyberScoop</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Regulatory</span><span class="src-count">5</span><span>AI regulation, defense regulatory bodies</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Gov Contracting</span><span class="src-count">4</span><span>GovExec, Federal News Network</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Economic</span><span class="src-count">4</span><span>Bloomberg, FT, economic indicators</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Crisis</span><span class="src-count">4</span><span>ReliefWeb, UNHCR, humanitarian feeds</span></div>
                    <div class="source-row"><span class="src-cat">Energy</span><span class="src-count">4</span><span>EIA, energy security sources</span></div>
                </div>

                <div class="sources-side">
                    <div class="credibility-card">
                        <span class="cc-label">Credibility Tiers</span>
                        <div class="cc-tier"><span class="cc-tier-num">T1</span><div><strong>Authoritative</strong><p>Reuters, AP, AFP, Bloomberg, government agencies (White House, Pentagon, State, UN), IAEA, WHO, UNHCR</p></div></div>
                        <div class="cc-tier"><span class="cc-tier-num">T2</span><div><strong>Major Outlets</strong><p>BBC, The Guardian, CNN, Al Jazeera, Financial Times, CNBC</p></div></div>
                        <div class="cc-tier"><span class="cc-tier-num">T3</span><div><strong>Specialty</strong><p>Think tanks, defense outlets, Bellingcat, regional security media</p></div></div>
                        <div class="cc-tier"><span class="cc-tier-num">T4</span><div><strong>Aggregators</strong><p>Hacker News, tech aggregators, ArXiv</p></div></div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="apis-card">
                        <span class="cc-label">External Data APIs</span>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>UCDP / HAPI</strong> &mdash; Uppsala Conflict Data Program</li>
                            <li><strong>GDELT</strong> &mdash; events, language, tone</li>
                            <li><strong>EIA</strong> &mdash; U.S. Energy Information Administration</li>
                            <li><strong>World Bank</strong> &mdash; tech readiness indicators</li>
                            <li><strong>YouTube Live</strong> &mdash; auto-discovered city webcams</li>
                            <li><strong>FIRMS / NASA</strong> &mdash; satellite fire detection</li>
                            <li><strong>AIS Maritime</strong> &mdash; vessel tracking</li>
                            <li><strong>ADS-B</strong> &mdash; military flight tracking</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── TIER-1 COUNTRY COVERAGE (LIGHT) ── -->
    <section class="section coverage-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header reveal">
                <span class="section-label">Tier-1 Country Coverage</span>
                <h2>31 Nations at the Core of Allied Defense Posture</h2>
                <p>The countries most relevant to allied defense, the strategic competition, and the active conflict environment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="coverage-grid reveal">
                <div class="coverage-group">
                    <span class="cov-cat cov-cat-allied">NATO / Allied</span>
                    <div class="cov-flags">
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇺🇸 USA</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇬🇧 UK</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇫🇷 France</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇩🇪 Germany</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇵🇱 Poland</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇦🇺 Australia (Five Eyes)</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="coverage-group">
                    <span class="cov-cat cov-cat-adversary">Adversarial / Contested</span>
                    <div class="cov-flags">
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇷🇺 Russia</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇨🇳 China</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇮🇷 Iran</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇰🇵 North Korea</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="coverage-group">
                    <span class="cov-cat cov-cat-conflict">Active Conflict Zones</span>
                    <div class="cov-flags">
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇺🇦 Ukraine</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇸🇾 Syria</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇾🇪 Yemen</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇲🇲 Myanmar</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇸🇩 Sudan</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇪🇹 Ethiopia</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇨🇩 DRC</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇸🇴 Somalia</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇦🇫 Afghanistan</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇮🇶 Iraq</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇱🇾 Libya</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇳🇬 Nigeria</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇱🇧 Lebanon</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="coverage-group">
                    <span class="cov-cat cov-cat-regional">Strategic / Regional Powers</span>
                    <div class="cov-flags">
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇮🇳 India</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇵🇰 Pakistan</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇸🇦 Saudi Arabia</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇹🇷 Turkey</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇦🇪 UAE</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇧🇷 Brazil</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇻🇪 Venezuela</span>
                        <span class="cov-flag">🇹🇼 Taiwan</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── PLATFORM ARCHITECTURE (DARK) ── -->
    <section class="section arch-section">
        <div class="arch-bg"></div>
        <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
            <div class="section-header reveal">
                <span class="dark-label">Platform Architecture</span>
                <h2>Edge-First. Browser-Heavy. Serverless in Between.</h2>
                <p>Lightweight by design. Heavy computation pushed to the analyst's device. Vercel Edge handles the rest.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-table reveal">
                <div class="arch-row arch-head">
                    <span>Layer</span>
                    <span>Technology</span>
                </div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">Frontend</span><span>TypeScript SPA (Vite), no framework &mdash; custom Panel component system</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">Map Engine</span><span>DeckGL 9.2 + MapLibre GL &mdash; 34 toggleable intelligence layers</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">ML Inference</span><span>ONNX Runtime Web + HuggingFace Transformers (browser-side, no server roundtrip)</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">Serverless API</span><span>Vercel Edge Functions &mdash; 13+ endpoints (RPC router, RSS proxy, email gate, story generation, OG metadata, YouTube discovery, EIA proxy)</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">Data Store</span><span>Upstash Redis (caching, email gate, session state)</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">LLM Integration</span><span>Groq (Llama 3.3 70B) for country intel briefs on demand</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">Analytics</span><span>PostHog + Vercel Analytics + Sentry error tracking</span></div>
                <div class="arch-row"><span class="arch-layer-label">i18n</span><span>i18next (multi-language ready)</span></div>
